description.plain:
Terry Wallace (born March 23, 1994), better known as Tee Grizzley, is a platinum-selling hip hop recording artist from Detroit, Michigan.

Raised on Joy Road in West Detroit, Tee Grizzley was originally known as ASBH Tee of the Allstars BallHard crew. Years later, Grizzley burst back onto the hip hop scene with the release of his debut single, “First Day Out,” in 2016 after serving almost three years in prison for home invasion. The song quickly became a viral hit and led to Grizzley signing a deal with 300 Entertainment under the label Atlantic Records.

Tee then went on to release multiple singles, including the platinum-selling record “From the D to the A,” featuring Lil Yachty. In April 2017, Tee Grizzley released his debut commercial mixtape, My Moment, which hit #44 on the Billboard 200 chart even without a guest feature. In December of 2017, Tee followed up the success of My Moment with Bloodas, a collaborative mixtape with Chicago rapper Lil Durk.

In May of 2018, Grizzley released his first official album, Activated, which hit the top ten of the Billboard 200 list.

In November of 2018, Grizzley released Still My Moment. A much anticipated follow up to My Moment, the mixtape features the likes of Chance the Rapper, Quavo, Offset, and Lil Pump.

Laced with menacing beats and executive production from Timbaland, Grizzley released his 2nd studio album, Scriptures on the 7th of June in 2019. He released his third project, The Smartest, one year later in June of 2020.

Grizzley first previewed the song on Twitter a week before its release saying:

description.plain: Tee Grizzley and Meek Mill have been working on many projects before Meek was sentenced to prison in November. They came out with their first collab song, Beef, gave a small glimpse of what type of music fans would be hearing from the two. The song was also previewed before at concerts and on social media over the Summer of 2017 and its release has been long awaited. Unfortunately, Meek is imprisoned for 2-4 years (as of November, 2017), more about it here. This is why throughout the song there are many references to the unjust sentence with lines and adlibs such as “Free Meek”. The song is a remix of Grizzley’s well-known, “breakout” song as it has gave him a big boost in the rap game.

description.plain:
“Trenches” marks the first collaboration between two of Detroit’s biggest rappers, Tee Grizzley and Big Sean. The track is the 3rd track off of Grizzley’s 5th album, The Smartest, and was produced by renowed producer and frequent Big Sean collaborator, Hit-Boy.

Over a hard, distorted, piano beat, Big Sean and Tee  rap about their own origin stories in Detroit. Sean talks about his crew and what he brings to the table, while Tee talks about how he came up from nothing, how he has to keep real people by him, and about what he wants to achieve.

description.plain:
Tee Grizzley reunites with Lil Durk on the melodic “White Lows Off Designer.” It serves as their first collaboration in a little more than two years. The song’s title refers to the low vulcanized sneakers, shoes from Virgil Abloh’s designer brand, Off-White.

The two artists discuss the problems and hardships that they faced in their respective hometowns of Detroit and Chicago. Their verses specifically focus on being in jail, usage of drugs, and being let down by people who they thought were their friends.
